### üîå Power & Other Notes
- **All grounds must be common** (tie module GNDs to ESP32 GND). :contentReference[oaicite:31]{index=31}  
- **I2C bus:** SDA = **GPIO 21**, SCL = **GPIO 22** (shared by MAX30100 and MLX90614).   
- **10¬µF capacitor** between **EN** and **GND** to help automatic USB upload/reset. :contentReference[oaicite:33]{index=33}

---

## Final notes & action items
1. **MLX90614 power:** confirm your exact MLX90614 breakout module. If it explicitly accepts 3.3V on VDD and the I¬≤C lines are 3.3V, **use 3.3V** to avoid level mismatches. If the breakout expects 5V and uses level shifting for I¬≤C, 5V per thesis is fine ‚Äî just confirm with the breakout datasheet. (thesis shows VDD‚Üí5V). :contentReference[oaicite:34]{index=34}  
2. All other pin mappings in the README schematic **match the thesis** (MAX30100, AD8232, ST7789, buzzer, capacitor). 

